metadata.name: Flamingo, KB
metadata.description:
Digital Photograph by Rodrigo Gaya Villar.

Jan 1, 2020 - Key Biscayne, FL - Along the tranquil shoreline marking the barrier island's eastern boundary, an inflatable flamingo lonely floats bathed in the sunset light shining across southern end. 

Once a symbol for community, the native flamingos haven't bread in the area for decades.

Edition: 1/1
Medium: Digital Photography 
File Type: PNG
Size: 3112x4668
Megapixels: 14.5
